{
  "texts": [
    "ChatGPT did not split the long paragraphs into subheadings, which was implemented in some of the student responses as a strategy to ease understanding.",
    "Since the subject was primarily focused on the Indian context, the evaluators also opined that ChatGPT did not cover this context adequately in the responses.",
    "The more Western-oriented responses might be because ChatGPT is mainly trained based on English content available on the internet.",
    "Supporting this hypothesis, OpenAI has also noted that the role of ChatGPT in a classroom setting is currently biased toward Western settings, while non-Western perspectives are inequitably incorporated within the model [20].",
    "The scope for expansion of the perspectives beyond borders is possible in the future.The responses to the epidemiological questions need to be elaborately discussed with more clarity using examples and illustrations."
  ]
}